Daphni takes over NTS for a three-party residency, ahead of the release of his new LP, 'Butterfly'.

nts1.n: ZEL ZELE W/ DEBORA IPEKEL & ECE DUZGIT (R)
nts1.d: London & Istanbul based record label Zel Zele takes us on a monthly ride to earthly wonders and cosmic adventures. Bite the lip take the trip!

Part of the NTS family since day dot, Moxie has held her Wednesday show since the stations first broadcasts. Inviting esteemed guests for interviews & mixes and breaking new, unreleased music, she’s got your Wednesday afternoons covered… Tune in to hear anything from Soulful House, Garage, Afro beats and all the way through to rolling techno.

After work fun and global tunes with Tash LC and guests every other Wednesday
From the host: "Recorded in November 2025 at The Carpet Shop Peckham at the Club Yeke edition of Tash's residency"
Theo Motive takes you on a monthly journey through upfront Hip Hop, Beats, Grime, Bass & everything in between.

nts1.n: Steven Julien Presents: The Apron Show
nts1.d: The Apron Records boss takes his anything goes approach to an continually surprising hour of radio every month, featuring everything from dusty leftfield house to energetic jazz, and anything else that he's feeling.
The London-based DJ brings his hybrid club sound fusing UK rhythms, highspeed techno and R&B and pop references to the NTS airwaves.
London-based DJ Imogen takes on the NTS airwaves, bouncing between fuzzy electro and punishing techno.

nts1.n: THE NCA SHOW W/ Digital Death Penalty
nts1.d: NCA is a London tape label specialising in experimental, techno and hip-hop, co-run by Brassfoot. Tune in to his monthly NCA Show for exclusives and jams from across the range - techno, house, hip-hop and more…
Regular transmissions from two of Glasgow's most idiosyncratic & knowledgable DJs.

The NTS Breakfast Show w/ Bill Brewster

nts2.d:
Transmissions from the Outer Rim/Inner Edge.
“you know the gates themselves are made of flood.”
-Nadia Marcus

Explorations” is an attempt to shed light on offbeat music from India and around the world. Digging In India aka Nishant Mittal is a music archivist, DJ and record store owner based in New Delhi.
From the host "Cover versions/remakes of songs by legendary artists such as Micael Jackson, Donna Summer, Bob Marley, Madonna & others in Hindi, Urdu, Arabic, Tamil & more!"
Ethiopian-Somalian MC, singer and artist Bananasoverdose sweeps us off to pre-civil war Somalia, a golden era for music in the country, featuring an hour of hits and lesser known tracks.
"Shakshouka" is a dialectal arabic word used in North Africa to reflect an unexpected mixture of elements that wouldn’t naturally go together.
Prolific London based DIY & lo-fi pop producer Keel Her heads to the studio for a show once a month.

nts2.n: THE BADDIS SOUND W/ DANNIELLA DEE & MIA KODEN
nts2.d: Inspired by the iconic reggae & ska sounds of her home, singer & producer Danniella Dee shares a monthly crate of dub-wise selections, soul-soothing rocksteady, and heavyweight roots to the studio.

Tune into Martyn's monthly show on 2 for some delectable jazz treats from over the Atlantic.
From the host: "Martyn's back with more 60/70s modal and avant garde selections fresh for the new year"

Cultural critic and curator Timmhotep Aku explores the intersections of black music, life, metaphor, and meaning through songs and found audio footage.
From the host: "Contrary to popular belief, NY rappers loved the South in the late '90s and early aughts. Sure, southern rap had its haters in the five boroughs but forward-thinking artists like Foxy Brown, Nore, and Jay-Z were embracing their country cousins and making bangers."

nts2.n: Aloha Got Soul w/ Roger Bong
nts2.d:
An exploration into obscure, underground, and lesser known music from Hawaii, bound not by genre or generation but by a connection to the islands. Hosted by Roger Bong of Aloha Got Soul, a record label and record store in Honolulu.
From the host: "Woke up this morning with "Summer" by Audy Kimura stuck in my head. This month's show follows a melancholic, AOR vibe with a sense of loss or longing."

nts2.n: THE WINDMILLS OF YOUR MIND w/ Taylor Rowley
nts2.d: DJ & music supervisor Taylor Rowley forages for the forgotten musical past every month, uncovering soundtracks, psych rock & other treasures.

Chicago-based archival record label, The Numero Group, host a deep-digging once a month show. Expect comprehensive round ups from their crates, picking out the best old music and reissues, as well as some jubilant nerdy record chat.

Colombia-born, NYC based artist Ela Minus goes deep on the inspirations behind her new album DIA in a series of shows, exploring the project and its surrounding sonics from a spectrum of different angles.

nts2.n: Beyond The Clouds w/ Masha Mar (R)
nts2.d: Going full Beyond the Clouds with this 8 year anniversary show - dub, cosmic, balearic & beyond

subtle.d: Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.

subtle.n: Out of Phase With Sam Ling

subtle.d: Sessions w/ Amy B is an underground multi-genre music show, showcasing the most prolific guests from all corners of the music industry.

Originally linking up in Wellington and playing shows with the Breaking Beats crew, Swampman and Zero Crumbs have reunited – bringing their smooth mixing and flexible selections to East London. 

In their monthly show, the pair explore the deep, dark, and soulful ends of DNB. Expect fresh underground tunes, deep cut classics, and a bit of banter in Kiwi accents.

subtle.n: Dun Roamin w/ Tomi From Brockley

subtle.d:
Midlands born, London based producer and DJ influenced by UK funky, broken techno, garage and early dubstep. 

Has released on Keysound recordings, RKS, eatmybeat, ec2a, Durkle Disco and Dimsum records

2Step Selects is a monthly show hosted by the Choki Biki Records crew. Founded in Dublin, Ireland, CBR consists of DJ Sharpson, 2step.png, Frame Shift, and MICK. The show consists of an all round breaks, electro, ukg and jungle hour, followed by an Irish showcase, demonstrating all the best Ireland has to offer collective/party/Dj & Producer wise!

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy

Peak Oil records presents ‘tipping point’; a monthly journey through the record collections of brian and brion. Leaving no good genre unturned, enjoy two hours of esoterica, conversation and guests.
